<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently Zend_Validate_Date uses the following regular expression:
/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}/
In this approach all the strings with a proper date at the beginning and any text at the end (such as: "2007-08-02something") are validated as a proper date.
The regular expression which should be used in Zend_Validate_Date is following:
/^\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}$/</p>

    </div>
